The paper deals with private computation, which is a topic in cryptography and security (cs.CR). It also involves encoding techniques, such as Reed-Solomon codes, which fall under information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses distributed computing and server behavior, which are topics in distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper mentions the use of secret sharing, which is a technique commonly used in cryptography and coding theory (cs.CC).
